--- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com, stack &lt;stack@a...&gt; wrote:
&gt; Ahnu Nahki wrote:
&gt; 
&gt; &gt;I want to find out the distance from a home page, to another page on
&gt; &gt;the site, how many links away is that page from the start of the site.
&gt; &gt;We have an application that requires the page depth of a site. We used
&gt; &gt;to determine it using an old crawler we have. We&#39;d like to use
&gt; &gt;heritrix to do the same thing, but I dont know what in the API I use
&gt; &gt;to determine how far a page is from the starting page. Some one had
&gt; &gt;mentioned hopsfilter class, but I really dont understand it or have
&gt; &gt;any proper documentation to go by. Any help would be greatly
appreciated.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;Regards,
&gt; &gt;Ahnu
&gt; &gt;  
&gt; &gt;
&gt; Would you be asking these questions post-crawl? There is perl script in 
&gt; the bin directory called hoppath.pl that looks at crawl.log files.  If 
&gt; you give it a URI, it will list the referrers the crawler followed to 
&gt; get from initial &#39;seed&#39; URI to queried URI (See the head of the script 
&gt; for notes on edits that need to be made before it can be run).
&gt; 
&gt; Otherwise, regards what to use in the API, Heritrix has classes that 
&gt; bundle URIs and their state (CandidateURI, CrawlURI).  Part of the
state 
&gt; kept by a URI is the path from the initial &#39;seed&#39; URI.  See 
&gt; CandidateURI#pathFromSeed here 
&gt;
http://crawler.archive.org/xref/org/archive/crawler/datamodel/CandidateURI.html#57).

&gt; See here in CrawlScope for an example of counting hops: 
&gt;
http://crawler.archive.org/xref/org/archive/crawler/framework/CrawlScope.html#247.
&gt; 
&gt; Yours,
